{"questionId":"32943777","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For extra support, Jamali decides to attach a rope, with length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> , to the tent at a point, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> , on the edge <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AT</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The rope will be fixed to the ground at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>, such that:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the rope, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mi>PQ</mi></mfenced></math>, is straight</li>\n<li>points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> lie on a straight line</li>\n<li>\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>°</mo></math>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is shown in the diagrams.<br><br></p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/a9203a7974a9eb191fe4ca3c98b52fc5a882f7fb.png\" width=\"629\" height=\"249\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the area of the base</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong> &nbsp; (Use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></math>)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find area of one triangle using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>23</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>23</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3826</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>27</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A0M0A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn></math> or equivalent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong>(Use of altitude)</p>\n<p>(altitude is) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>59807</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find area of one triangle using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>h</mi></math> with their altitude<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>23</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>23</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3826</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>27</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A0M0A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>3</mn></math> or equivalent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong> (Finding the area of a trapezoid)</p>\n<p>(altitude of one trapezoid is)&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>59807</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find area of one trapezoid using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>)</mo><mi>h</mi></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math> &nbsp; <strong>OR</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>27</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>23</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>23</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3826</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>27</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"32943777","referenceCode":"24N.2.SL.TZ1.5bi","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the area of the base","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, midpoints","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig"],"memberSectionIds":[],